programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: It is the most extraordinary case diplomat Tom Walter has ever seen - 18 and 16 year-old Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson have been abandoned by their parents and left to fend for themselves.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's judgement day for abandoned Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson. After hours of questioning, Indonesian Immigration officials have confiscated the boy's passports and put them under strict house arrest.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: 59-year-old Joanne came to Thailand for a body makeover. She's had a tummy tuck and liposuction to look her best for her daughter's wedding. She loses her passport and the wound from her tummy tuck gets infected, Joanne finds herself stuck in Thailand.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Tiger 800 XC
programme.desc: Motorcycles explores the British way to drive. Of course, that can’t go without talking about the British cult brand Triumph. Our expert Ralf Schütze reviews their Tiger 800 and Tiger 1050.

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferruccio Lamborghini

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferry Porsche

programme.title: Motorheads: Walther Roehrl

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans-Joachim Stuck

programme.title: Motorheads: Stephane Peterhansel

programme.title: Motorheads: Alois Ruf

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans Herrmann

programme.title: Motorheads: Sabine Schmitz

programme.title: Motorheads: Prince Leopold von Bayern

programme.title: Motorheads: Henry Ford

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Bliss
programme.desc: Lili is given a psychotropic drug called "bliss" via a Taelon device. They discover it is widespread. With an instantly strong addictive property, the addicts are dying within 48 hours. The investigation leads Liam and Sandoval to Ireland.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Highjacked
programme.desc: With a reporter on board, the Taelon mother ship is highjacked into interdimensional space. Liam is the prime suspect, causing an even bigger rift between Da'an and Zo'or. As the ship floats, lost in space, they must find the real culprit.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Defector
programme.desc: A shuttle crashes on a beach after being pursued by a second Taelon piloted shuttle. When Liam locates the survivor (a Taelon called Belleye), he claims to want to help the Resistance take back Earth from the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak
programme.desc: Augur is recruited by a Taelon weapons project, but the others are worried about his involvement. When the project is launched earlier than originally planned to fight a Jiridian fleet, the Earth is in danger.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crossfire
programme.desc: As the election draws near, Liam believes Zo'or is trying to have Jonathan Doors murdered. The Resistance worries that an attack is imminent at the final debate. Julia mobilizes a group to protect Doors against Liam's wishes.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crackdown
programme.desc: An unknown woman saves Augur and Liam from the raids on the Resistance. Lili sabotages the mother ship, but Zo'or stops its total destruction. Lili is reportedly dead. The investigation on the President's shooter continues.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Vanished
programme.desc: Some who were detained during the Resistance sweep have not reappeared after their release. Lili is taken to a lab run by Sandoval and implanted. Renee tries to help Liam find the missing people.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Emancipation
programme.desc: A group posing as volunteers attacks using a stolen skrill prototype that does not require an implant to control. It is discovered that the skrill queen is also missing. The investigation leads to a resistance group called Black Wednesday.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Niddry Street Vaults

programme.title: Most Haunted: Jedburgh Castle

programme.title: Most Haunted: S.S. Great Britain

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Dream of Wild Horses
programme.desc: The patriarch of a ranch family feels he's too old to rein in some wild horses.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: In With the "In" Crowd

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Crystal Clear

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Teacher Learns A Lesson

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: First Class Male

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Serving Up a New Look
programme.desc: Dirk has been a busy restaurant owner for as long as he can remember. Long hours running three different establishments kept him from ever having time to take care of himself. Now, he's retired and ready to get on with life, but can't seem to get a date.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back to Hog Heaven
programme.desc: Once comfortable on the back of her husband's Harley, this biker babe has lost all confidence in her looks. Now her aging appearance is keeping her from the fun things in life – all that used to make her happy.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Shopping For a New Look
programme.desc: Karyn is a busy working wife and mother of three, whose current frumpy appearance isn't matching the way she feels inside. It's the goal of our experts to fashion Karyn a more youthful, trendsetting look as we try make her look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 35 year old Richard Power was living life to the limits – and it showed. A year later, we recap Richard's rocky relationship with our femme fatale of flair – and see whether a catch-up with Nicky will set things straight.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringing Out The Spunk
programme.desc: Cat has a dream job working with rock stars and she lost 125 pounds with diet and exercise. She's worked hard to get where she is, but its left her looking more 30-something than 20-something. Our team is ready to jam on her makeover and do what it takes.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!
programme.desc: Dorothy is a single mother of two whose life changed recently when her long time employer closed its doors. Dorothy knows that years of smoking and the stress of raising her sons alone has aged her.
programme.sub-title: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Make Under
programme.desc: Hair stylist Dawn has a big personality that's hidden her perpetual weight problem. She needs to slim down her appearance. With help, Dawn sheds pounds and years off of her appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sky Hag To Sky Hottie

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: High Flying Look
programme.desc: Joanne's been soaring the blue skies for the past 20 years as a pilot. Flying at high altitudes in the bright sun all these years has left her skin damaged and wrinkled. Watch our experts bring out her feminine side and drop the years from her appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Peeling Back The Years
programme.desc: Joan suffers from adult acne and her obsessive-compulsive disorder prompts her to pick her face constantly. Her job as host of a theme park show keeps her in the public eye, so looking her best is essential.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Smokin’ Hot
programme.desc: After losing her mom at a young age, Fayleen took care of her younger siblings and the stress of tough times caused her to go gray at 18. Now she has her own family and Fayleen wants to look good for her children.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Saying "I Do" To A New Look
programme.desc: Maggie, a sassy gal from Scotland, is about to marry a man 13 years younger then her! This mother of two has found love, but doesn't want to look like she is the mom giving the groom away when she walks down the aisle. Our team is up for the challenge.
programme.sub-title: Saying "I Do" To A New Look

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New lodges nearly break the family, but they learn that it's the animals which make Leopard's Den a success.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny needs an assistant but fails to see that she's right under his nose; Sarah finds out that she needs her mum.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den expands and DuPlessis becomes a grandfather after a close-call with an angry elephant.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 1
programme.desc: Muriwai lifeguard's first rescue of the season is of an unexpected nature and on a remote part of the beach. Lifeguards rush to the aid of a distraught 18-year-old girl whose been sucked into a treacherous hole.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 2
programme.desc: Lifeguards struggle to keep swimmers safe as swift rips sweep them out of the flagged area. But for one boogie boarder it's too late. The young guns are put to the test as a surfer is pounded by huge swells and dragged across jagged rocks.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 3
programme.desc: It's looking like another perfect day for the mounting crowd at Muriwai Beach, but lifeguards soon have a crisis on their hands as a full scale search is mounted for a young boy.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 4
programme.desc: A surfer washes up on Muriwai Beach and lifeguards are unsure what's wrong with him. Lifeguards could be forced to shut the beach because of an invasion of a swarm of jellyfish.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 5
programme.desc: With the summer season in full swing the veteran guards decide to teach the Rookie's some new tricks. A shark sighting has the entire beach on full alert. And the relentless rips prove too much for one Canadian tourist.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 6
programme.desc: Inviting surf conditions cause chaos's as the mix of boards and swimmers ends in tears. Could engine failure be disastrous for Muriwai lifeguards as a group of inexperience surfers are swept out to sea. And the pounding surf shows the IRB crew whose boss.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 7

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 8

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 9

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 10
programme.desc: It's business as usual for lifeguards on the final patrol of the summer and the stormy weather is making Muriwai look like a scene out of Gothic Beach. Flat Rock causes bloodshed as a rookie guard takes on the elements.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper crew races to save a woman with a rare disease who's in danger of suffocating from uncontrollable muscle spasms; a badly burnt toddler at Cooks Beach needs an urgent airlift to hospital.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Ice Action Finland

programme.desc: More power and yet better fuel economy? With chip tuning this is supposed to be possible. We want to check this out and send two teams on a road trip with a difference. From Uhingen near Stuttgart in Germany, we travel to Barcelona and back.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: New Car Purchase Experience

programme.title: Motorvision Special: 90 Years BMW Motor Bike

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bump In the Night
programme.desc: When a pretty, young pilot is found in bed, bound and with a bullet in her head, Lt. Joe Kenda must determine if this was a random assault or payback for something that happened in the skies.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Manifesto

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Knock Knock
programme.desc: A gathering of friends turns deadly when two gunmen shoot William Davis in the head. Kenda and his team dig into his past and start to suspect someone in William’s circle is lying.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Written in Blood
programme.desc: A community is shocked when Antoine McKenzie is brazenly shot outside an auto parts store in broad daylight. The only lead left for Lt. Joe Kenda is a final message written in the victim’s own blood.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: I Will Hunt You Down
programme.desc: When two escaped inmates surface in Colorado Springs, it’s up to Lt. Joe Kenda and his Fugitive Unit to bring them to justice.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder in a Bottle

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: John 3:16

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Body in the Freezer
programme.desc: A meeting between two businessmen leaves one shot in the face. Things seem cut and dry until Lt. Kenda realizes the “victim” could actually be the aggressor, shot struggling over his own gun.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cricket and Hemingway & Rigby

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: How to Raise the Perfect Dog

programme.sub-title: How to Raise the Perfect Dog

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Woof and Wheels
programme.desc: People and their dogs descended on a local PETCO to meet producers in the hopes of a session with Cesar Millan. Meet two of the problem pooches. Can Cesar dial down the bad behavior of these terrors?

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Beagle Mania, Rescue Me… Rescue You
programme.desc: At six years old, beagle Gizmo has become very aggressive. Jennifer Lee Pryor runs Pryor’s Planet, a rescue organization to honor her late husband, comedian Richard Pryor.
programme.sub-title: Beagle Mania, Rescue Me… Rescue You

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Maxwell, Brooklyn, and Tipper
programme.desc: A spoiled Welsh Sealyham Terrier has dominance issues; an excitable English Mastiff has behavioral issues, and a territorial Tibetan Terrier needs help accepting other dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Caged Shepherd, Tinkling Terrier
programme.desc: Troy, a German Shepherd, is aggressive towards the other animals in his home. Roxie, a Rat Terrier, is so timid that when a sudden noise disturbs her, she’ll pee on the floor.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Sooner & Trace, and Casanova
programme.desc: Not a lover, but a fighter, a young dog attacks other dogs while on leash. Two formerly friendly sibling dogs are now at each others’ throats. Can Cesar keep these dogs in line?

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cotton, Ricky, and Lila & Duke
programme.desc: An American Eskimo watchdog who takes his role too far; a Shibu Inu with a mean streak; a boxer who was attached by another dog one day in the park, and has since become more aggressive.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Cleanser/Tanner
programme.desc: Ever since she was twelve Crystle has been obsessed with eating household cleanser. Samantha is addicted to tanning and visits multiple tanning salons in order to get her fix.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Bathes in Bleach/Eats Plastic
programme.desc: Kailyn has eaten plastic every day for more than eleven years, consuming more than 150 pounds. Meanwhile, Gloria, 28, has taken her addiction to bleach to the extreme by bathing in it daily.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Carrying My Husband’s Urn
programme.desc: Casie has been so shocked by the sudden death of her husband, Shawn, that she takes his urn everywhere she goes. But she has now started eating his ashes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sniffs Pine Cleaner/Road Kill Addict
programme.desc: Jillian is addicted to smelling pine cleaner and can't go more than 15 minutes without a fix, using up to six bottles a week. Scott is obsessed with picking up dead animals from the road.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Cat Food/Smells Moth Balls
programme.desc: Mary has taken her addiction to cat food to the extreme, consuming 900 cat treats and several cans of food every day. Meanwhile, Alicia has been addicted to smelling mothballs for 15 years.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: 5,000 Kids_Tickled Pink
programme.desc: Pat and Joe are passionate about their extreme collection of over 5,000 infamous kid dolls. Kitty Kay Sera is completely obsessed with the color pink. She even wears pink clothes and eats pink food.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Ventriloquist/Cat Lady
programme.desc: April's addiction to her puppets has gotten so strong she can't go anywhere without them. Debbie is severely allergic to cats, but has over twenty of them, leaving her in isolation.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Detergent/Strongman
programme.desc: 19-year-old Tempestt eats detergent up to seven times a day, not to mention the soap she eats in the shower. Meanwhile, Jeff is addicted to strongman competitions training up to six hours a day.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Coffee Enemas/Licks Cats
programme.desc: Trina and her husband Mike have done nearly 7,000 coffee enemas over the last two and a half years. Lisa has been addicted to licking her cat and eating clumps of its hair for three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict
programme.desc: Nathaniel has been in a relationship with his car for nearly five years, taking it out on dates, buying it gifts, and even getting intimate with it. Jaye has been addicted to snorting baby powder.
programme.sub-title: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Hair Puller/Shoe Fanatic
programme.desc: Showcases a woman addicted to shoes, while another is addicted to pulling her hair and eating the follicle.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: This Little Piggy_All Dolled Up
programme.desc: Sharon’s collection of pig items has exceeded 6,000 and adorns almost every square inch of her home. Rebecca’s obsession with Barbie dolls includes styling her own hair and wardrobe to match her dolls.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: The Cat's House_My Oval Office
programme.desc: Frances and Bob share their house with nine felines who they raise like children. Ron is obsessed with U.S. presidents. He’s even built a replica of the oval office in his home.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Troll Takeover_Stuffing Animals
programme.desc: The Smith family has a collection of 213 stuffed and mounted animals throughout their home. Michelle’s obsession with trolls threatens her relationship with her family.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Remote Coves
programme.desc: Charlie and Toni are outdoor adventure junkies who want a home in Alaska that’s so remote they can catch their next meal from the ocean right off their front porch.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Homer Bound
programme.desc: Nathan and Lindsay are brand new to Alaska. They want a house similar to where Nathan’s pioneer grandfather lived, in the bayside town of Homer, surrounded by the great outdoors.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Life On A Mountain
programme.desc: Russ and Dana search for a home in the town of Girdwood, Alaska, at the base of towering Mount Alyeska. The views are spectacular, but the danger of an avalanches is real.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Guys Getaway
programme.desc: David Parks and Chris Erickson are best friends, and professional handymen. They want to buy a weekend getaway house in the wilds of Alaska, but they don’t want to spend a lot of money.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Juneau Waterfront
programme.desc: Chris and Heidi are marine adventurers who want Alaska’s marine wildlife right out their front door. They want to buy a home on the coveted waterfront of the oceanside city of Juneau.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Tiny Homes, Big Mountain
programme.desc: Pete and Martha have lived and worked in some of the wildest locations in the U.S. In Alaska they want an isolated home with views of the tallest peak in North America - Mount McKinley.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Dollars Or Drains
programme.desc: Texas native Colby wants an affordable home, but he’s in for a shock because, in Alaska, that means a dry cabin – with no running water. He doesn’t know anything about life without plumbing.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Dangerous Trails
programme.desc: Brandon and Hanna want a home on an isolated lake far into the Alaskan wild, where there’s no way in but off-roading through trails of mud or landing on water.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: No Roads In
programme.desc: Dave and Wendy want a remote cabin where they can escape to the Alaskan frontier way of life, places so hidden that the only way there is by off-road vehicle and no outhouse is safe from hungry bears.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Jaws, Claws & Beaver Fever
programme.desc: Shane and Erica want a home in the Alaskan wild, where it’s so remote, the only way in is by a monster 8-wheeler. Homeowners beware! Bears attack the properties and beavers infect the drinking water.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Hot Tubs and Gators
programme.desc: Duck, Lathan, & Flip are tired of traveling each weekend to their favorite place to enjoy bayou living. They’re willing to do anything to buy a home if they can hunt gators right out their back door.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Lakes for the Champ
programme.desc: “Catfish” Jack Clampit and his daughter, Amanda, love hand-grabbing catfish, so he and Amanda are searching for a camp that will accommodate both their families…and their appetite for catfish.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Starter Homes
programme.desc: Josh McIntire is an avid duck hunter and fisherman and he hopes to find a house where he can do just that. He’s bringing his life-long best friend, Hanna, for guidance.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Rolling on the River
programme.desc: Bryan Fassbender and Stephanie Robichaux are self described work-a-holics who just want to have a weekend houseboat on the Pearl River, and are willing to live off the grid.

programme.title: Baywatch: Liquid Assets
programme.desc: CJ befriends Max, a homeless eccentric who claims that he was once a famous Hollywood Costume designer. When Max dies suddenly, CJ learns he was rich and has left her $4 million in his will. Manny joins junior lifeguards.

programme.title: Baywatch: Windswept
programme.desc: At the annual Baywatch Lifeguard Bachelor Auction, Mitch is "bought" for $5,000 by a wealthy socialite. The relationship gets complicated when they get stranded on an island and their social status is reversed. Cody joins a local roller hockey team.

programme.title: Baywatch: Scorcher
programme.desc: LA is in the throes of a severe heat wave! Hundreds of thousands of people head to the beach. Lifeguarding gets more chaotic for the team when the Secret Service shows up to inform them that the President is going to go jogging on the beach.

programme.title: Baywatch: Beachblast
programme.desc: To sponsor the Special Olympics at the beach, Mitch hires MTV DJ Jenny McCarthy to throw "Beachblast:" a live televised tournament. After being evicted from his apartment, Cody moves in with CJ and Caroline, creating a surplus of sexual tension.

programme.title: Baywatch: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner
programme.desc: CJ's mother, a former Las Vegas showgirl, arrives in town seeking CJ's help to get away from her mobster ex-boyfriend. When CJ and her mom are held hostage on a remote beach, it is up to Mitch and Cody to rescue them.

programme.title: Baywatch: Let the Games Begin
programme.desc: Australia's Uncle Toby's International Ironman Competition comes to LA. The Baywatch girls think all is fair in sports and convince the guys that they should compete as equals, setting the stage for a series of pranks between the men and women.

programme.title: Baywatch: Buried
programme.desc: Controversy generated by Donna's appearance in Playboy magazine divides the Baywatch lifeguards. When an earthquake triggers a rockslide, burying a bus full of junior lifeguards, Mitch, Samantha, Cody and Donna try to rescue them.

programme.title: Baywatch: Search and Rescue
programme.desc: After rescuing a group of fishermen and tourists from a pier fire, Samantha and L.A. fire chief Captain Huntingdon form an elite joint Search and Rescue unit. Meanwhile, Cody asks CJ to paint his portrait, and Mitch receives some strange PI work.
